description.text:
A very simple &quot;I Love You&quot; sign language cookie cutter that measures 3.5&quot; (90mm) from index finger to base and 3-1/4&quot; (85mm) from pinkie to thumb and 1&quot; (25mm) high sides to support thicker cake-like cookies.  For demonstration purposes this was printed out in Hatchbox yellow PLA on a Robo R1+plus using an E3Dv6 hot end and Bondtech QR (v3) direct drive extruder.  I would recommend using an FDA approved filament such as <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.makergeeks.com/fosafdapla11.html" >http://www.makergeeks.com/fosafdapla11.html</a>, but I am not aware of any animals or humans dying from a PLA cut cookie (just don't do it commercially!)
Trivia - why is the sign &quot;I Love You&quot; what it is?  Well, the pinky finger is the letter &quot;I&quot;, the thumb and index finger is the letter &quot;L&quot; and the thumb and pinky form the letter &quot;Y&quot; in the sign language alphabet.  Get rid of the thumb you get bull..... turn it around you get &quot;rock on!&quot;, rid of the index finger and you have &quot;surfs on dude...&quot;
Enjoy!
